                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/471.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>336. Department informed by Spanish Embassy at this capital that several Spanish
                    subjects have been murdered and their houses <pb facs="0948" n="832"
                        xml:id="pg_832"/> plundered by Zapata forces. Please investigate and
                    telegraph facts.</p>
                <p>If such acts have been committed please bring to attention of appropriate
                    authorities and urgently insist that the guilty parties be adequately punished
                    and that proper steps be taken to prevent a recurrence of such crimes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
